📘 1. Quick Guide — Managing HubSpot Lists for Preload

You can reuse this internally or paste into your repo README.

🎯 Purpose

Control which contacts are available for:

matching
suggestions
ID-based updates
🧱 How to Add a New List
Step 1 — Create or Select List in HubSpot
Go to: Contacts → Lists
Create:
Static list (manual)
OR Active list (rule-based)

👉 Example:

Event – Transport Logistic 2026
VIP Contacts
Existing Customers
Step 2 — Get List ID

From URL:

https://app-eu1.hubspot.com/.../objectLists/19611
                                      ↑ THIS
Step 3 — Add to Backend ENV

In Scalingo:

HUBSPOT_LIST_IDS=19611,12345,67890
Step 4 — Deploy (or restart)

No code change needed.

⚠️ Rules / Best Practices
Keep lists focused (1k–5k contacts ideal)
Avoid dumping entire CRM into a list
Prefer:
event-specific lists
region-based lists
role-based lists
🧠 Mental Model

Lists define:

“Who is relevant for this context?”

Your system is no longer global—it is context-aware.
